<TITLE> New NSI chief named </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka Mar 16 (bdnews24.com)The government has appointed a new head of National Security Intelligence (NSI) replacing Maj Gen Shaikh Monirul Islam. A retired army officer, Manzur Ahmed, will run NSI on a two-year contract, the government said Monday. Ahmed, of the 2nd Short Service Commission, left the army as a brigadier general. Gen Islam, of the 6th Short Service Commission, will be director general at government think-tank BIISS.
